olive oil
1 packet Pizza Dough
2 clove garlic
½ Onion
1 carrot
2 packet diced bacon
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet tomato paste
¼ cup water
1 tsp brown sugar
20 g butter
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 apple
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)

• Preheat oven to 240°C / 220°C fan-forced.
• Keep pizza dough in packaging and place in a bowl of hot tap water (not boiling) until the dough is warm, 20 minutes.
• Split each ball of pizza dough into 6 even pieces, then set aside to rest for at least 1 hour, until dough increases in size (speed this up by covering the dough balls with a bowl).

TIP: The dough needs to be warm to increase in size. Resting the dough improves the pizza base texture.

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic and onion (see ingredients). Grate carrot.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 6-7 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).

• Add carrot and onion and cook until tender, 3-4 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, and add garlic, garlic & herb seasoning and tomato paste, and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water, brown sugar and butter, and cook until reduced, 2-3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.

Little cooks: Help measure out the water!

• Dust some flour over a clean surface. Flour your hands and a rolling pin, then stretch and roll each ball of dough into a 10cm circle.
• Transfer pizza bases to a lined oven tray.
• Divide bacon filling evenly across half of each base. Sprinkle over shredded Cheddar cheese. Fold pizza dough over the filling and seal the edges. Add a small hole at the top of the pizza pockets.
• Bake until pizza pockets are golden, 15-20 minutes.

TIP: Dusting the surface and your hands with flour helps prevent the dough from sticking.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice apple.
• In a large serving bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, apple, a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Help toss the salad.

• Divide cheesy bacon and hidden veggie pizza pockets between plates.
• Serve with apple salad. Enjoy!